	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all, I'm not really flaming Verant, just trying to understand their logic.  With all the other flames already posted for this weapon, I saw no reason to add another.  But, I ask a question about the choice of weapon type, and provide a valid argument against it being 1HB, and you feel the need to jump down my throat and give me crap for flaming Verant.  Sounds like some hypocracy to me.<br><br>In response to your "reasons", lets take a look at these.  Hmmm, its 1HB because scythes look cool?  That makes no sense.  So, why not make every scythe in the game a 1HB weapon?  To put it simply, because a blade on the end of a stick isn't a blunt weapon.  The primary purpose of a scythe is to cut, not to bash.  If it cuts, it's a slashing weapon, right?  Looks don't affect the function of a weapon, so this is an invalid argument.  It's like saying that a sword could be a 1HB weapon because it looks cool.  <br><br>As for your claim that they made it 1HB so necros can use it with a secondary slot item, this sounds like a decent reason, but given the fact that scythes aren't blunt weapons due to their nature, they should have made this a staff or some other truly blunt weapon.  Then, I wouldn't have asked this question.<br><br>Wow, amazing how people are so quick to flame other people when they can't answer their questions.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
