	   <tr><td colspan=2>Seams everyone has an opinion Good or Bad and is adamant in their stance.  For those below 45ish, it may look like a godsend, but by the time you are able to acquire it, it looks more like a joke.(litterally)<br><br>First, the GOOD :<br>Individually, the stats suck, but when viewed as a whole, on a single item, they are Quite impressive.<br><br>The +20 int means that you can swap out several pieces of INT gear for Resist/AC gear.<br><br>It is &lt;functionally&gt; weightless.  Weight 5.0, STR +5.<br><br>The entire quest yields an incredible ammount of experience.<br><br>Questing this will keep a bored character busy for a Looong time. ;)<br><br><br>Now, the BAD :<br>22/34 1hb - Useless - Excelent ratio, but casters after 50 who melee are either farming greens, bought their account on EBay and don't know any better, or are just plain stupid. :P<br><br>STR 5 - Unimportant - In the time it takes to do this quest (assuming you have a full team just waiting to help you) you can easily get enough cash to buy 8 tinkers bags.<br><br>STA 10 - Trivial - helps you hold your breath longer I suppose, but we have DMF anyway.[the HP boost by this is microscopic]<br><br>INT 20 - Trivial - If you don't already have 200 INT without this, you probably arent adequately equipped to Get it.<br><br>CHA 5 - Trivial - Only use for CHA a necro has is getting better prices with vendors. [No it does NOT effect NPC reactions or fear, these are both myths]<br><br>MR 10% - Fair - OK, Cant argue that MR is good for 30+ regardless of class.<br><br>Fire/Cold 5% - Poor - If you are fighting mobs with spells based on these (i.e. dragons) you want MORE than 5 in every slot anyway.<br><br>Poison/Disease 15% - Poor - May be more useful when Plane of Decay is opened.<br><br>HP 20 - Poor - In relation to most 1hand items 40+, this is pathetic.<br><br>Mana 80 - Great/Poor - depends how true the mana cap rumor is.<br><br>Effect Torment of Shadows - Poor - Darkness spells get 2 resists, and 9 second cast from an item?!  Only useful for pulling stationary mobs since mobiles will be out of range by the time it's cast.<br><br>Obtainability - Attrocious - The other epics are of aid to a group/guild. This one however only benifits the user.  Finding adequate numbers to obtain this, even with a lot of friends, will be VERY difficult.<br><br>Worst of all,  We're NECROMANCERS!! Vile, Evil, Masters of the Undead.  A ducky on a stick with cute lil bubbles comming out is the single biggest Insult Verant ever gave us!<br><br>Summary :<br>Compared to the other Epics, this is the worst.  It is harder to get, yet the resist stats are lower, the effect laughable in comparison, and will not benifit anyone but the user, so finding a team to acquire it is going to be next to impossible.<br><br>In itself, it is an incredible item.(if it IS a slap in the face by it's appearance)<br><br>A long cycle lifetap/leech or AE Fear would be more suitable.<br><br>The resists should be on par with the other Epics (+10vsAll for the bards' for example) and they NEED TO CHANGE THE GRAPHICS! =(<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
